Package: ggtaylor
Type: Package
Title: This package provides the geom_taylor() function for generating Taylor diagrams in ggplot2.
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R: 
    person("David", "LeBauer", , "dlebauer@gmail.com", role = c("aut", "cre"),
           comment = c(ORCID = "0000-0001-7228-053X"))
Description: A very simple package that implements geom_taylor() for ggplot2. 
    This function is used to generate Taylor diagrams, which are a way to 
    visualize the performance of one or more models or model configurations
    when compared to observations.
    Taylor, K. E. (2001), Summarizing multiple aspects of model performance in 
    a single diagram, J. Geophys. Res., 106(D7), 7183â€“7192, 
    [https://doi.org/10.1029/2000JD900719](doi:10.1029/2000JD900719).
